@startgantt
title Auth Refactor Sprint — Q2 2026

' --- Project frame ---
Project starts 2026-05-18

saturday are closed
sunday are closed
2026-05-25 is closed
2026-06-04 is closed
2026-06-22 to 2026-06-24 are closed
2026-06-23 is open

/' Block comment:
   This example exercises the full subset of PlantUML Gantt syntax
   supported by the renderer. Parallel streams converge at QA. '/

-- Discovery --
[Stakeholder workshop] as [workshop] lasts 2 days
[Tech spec] as [spec] starts at [workshop]'s end and lasts 4 days
[Vendor briefing] as [vend] starts 2026-05-21 and requires 1 week and 4 days
note bottom
Spec review with architects.
Confirm API contract before implementation starts.
end note

-- Implementation [2] --
[API endpoints]    as [api]    starts at [spec]'s end and lasts 7 days
[Auth middleware]  as [middle] starts at [spec]'s end and lasts 5 days
[Frontend wiring]  as [fe]     starts at [api]'s end and lasts 6 days
[Migration script] as [mig]    starts at [api]'s start + 2 days and lasts 4 days
[Security audit]   as [sec]    starts at [middle]'s end + 1 day and lasts 3 days
[Hardening window] as [hw]     starts 2026-06-22 and ends 2026-06-26
[Doc draft]        as [doc]    starts at [api]'s end and ends 2026-07-03

' --- pauses on (task gets paused on specific date and/or weekday) ---
[doc] pauses on 2026-06-25
[doc] pauses on monday

-- QA & Release --
[QA sweep]     as [qa]     starts 1 working day after [fe]'s end and lasts 3 days
[Bug buffer]   as [bugs]   starts at [qa]'s end and lasts 2 days then [Production deploy] lasts 1 days
[Release tag]                happens at [Production deploy]'s end
[Post-release monitoring] as [post] happens on 3 days after [Release tag]'s end

-- Reference forms --
' --- D+n relative Tagesnotation (Doku-Standard: D+0 = Project starts) ---
[Spike T+0]    as [spike0]   starts D+0 and lasts 2 days
[Spike T+10]   as [spike10]  starts D+10 and lasts 1 day
[Wrap-up]      as [wrap]     ends D+50 and requires 2 days

' --- ends DATE standalone und ends DATE + requires ---
[Audit deadline] ends 2026-07-15
[Compliance review] ends 2026-07-20 and requires 4 days

' --- occurs from [M1] to [M2] (Task-Span zwischen Milestones) ---
[Project lifespan] occurs from [Kick-off] to [Release tag]

' --- displays on same row as (Tasks/Milestones auf gleiche Y-Zeile) ---
[Parallel A] starts 2026-06-15 and lasts 3 days
[Parallel B] starts 2026-06-25 and lasts 2 days
[Parallel B] displays on same row as [Parallel A]
[Side note] happens 2026-07-05
[Side note] displays on same row as [Audit deadline]

' --- Simplified task succession: then am Zeilenende ---
[Phase one] requires 3 days then
[Phase two] requires 2 days then
[Phase three] requires 1 day

' --- Backward constraints (starts N (working) days before) ---
[Pre-flight check] starts 2 days before [workshop]'s start
[Vendor handover] starts 3 working days before [spec]'s end and lasts 1 day
[Mirror window] starts 1 day before [api]'s start and ends at [api]'s end

' --- end-anchor: requires N and ends at [Y]'s end ---
[Sync with api] requires 3 days and ends at [api]'s end

' --- Milestones (absolute / pivot variants + backward) ---
[Kick-off]    happens 2026-05-18
[QA gate]     happens at [qa]'s start
[Bug-bash]    happens at [Production deploy]'s end + 2 days
[Pre-kickoff] happens on 5 days before [Kick-off]'s start
[Heads-up]    happens on 2 working days before [workshop]'s start

